          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1695718924621-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1695718924621-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1695718924621-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-1695718924621-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chips are cooking, cut the <strong>free range</strong> <strong>chicken thighs</strong> into strips</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken strips</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>soy sauce</strong> then mix well until evenly coated</p><p>Add the<strong> cornflour</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the chicken is fully coated in the cornflour mixture – these are your<strong> coated chicken strips</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
